sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1799022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Device was designed and assembled using Synbiota's GENtle software and Rapid DNA Prototyping (RDP) system. The device consists of two parts, separated by a terminator.
Part 1: LsrR open reading frame, under the control of the Lac promoter and a medium RBS. Part 2: RFP under the control of pLsrA and a medium RBS.
When cultured in a LacI- strain or in the presence of IPTG, LsrR is produced, repressing pLsrA and preventing expression of RFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Will Shindel, Michael Flanagan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pLsrA and LsrR were synthesized by IDT using sequence data provided by EcoGene and converted into RDP format following Synbiota's RDP part creation protocol. All other parts were provided inside Synbiota's RDP assembly kit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1799002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Gene for the repressor LsrR, present in the E. coli LsrRK operon. Represses the pLsrA promoter, as well as its own promoter, pLsrR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Miranda Halle
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was synthesized from E. coli genomic data retrieved via EcoGene: http://www.ecogene.org/gene/EG13805

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1799000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Promoter for the E. coli LsrACDB operon. This promoter is repressed by LsrR, and derepressed by autoinducer 2 (AI-2) in the presence of LsrK.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Miranda Halle
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was synthesized from E. coli genomic data retrieved via EcoGene. It is based on, but not identical to, a part created by the 2011 Tokyo Tech iGEM team: http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K649100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Promoter begins with the start of its cAMP-CRP binding site and ends after the second key LsrR binding sequence.
